I"ß<p>This guide explains how you can manage your website users. Appart from the possibility of adding a new user, you can also edit, delete or mark an existing users as spam and view the ads or orders created by them.</p>

<p>To manage your website users, go to your panel, <strong>Users</strong> -&gt; <strong>Users</strong>.</p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/users.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/users.png" alt="users" />
</a></p>

<h2 id="actions">Actions</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Edit:</strong> Edit an username, email, description, status, <a href="//docs.yclas.com/roles-work-classified-ads-script/">role</a>, rate, password, etc.</li>
  <li><strong>Delete:</strong> Delete this user permanently.</li>
  <li><strong>View Ads:</strong> Display all the ads created by this user.</li>
  <li><strong>View Orders:</strong> Display all the orders placed by this user.</li>
  <li><strong>Mark as spam:</strong> Mark this user as spam. Check out <a href="//docs.yclas.com/activate-blacklist-works/">this guide</a> for more information.</li>
</ul>

